column5: Good fishing and thanks for posting Mike.  That area is getting more and more publicity over the last few years. Know of a few boats heading out there this fall for the first time.  Getting quite the buzz.  Trade ya a Musky Day for a Steelheading one, their even!

Nice fish!!  We rarely see musky reports like this anymore and they are always a pleasure to read.  My gf didn't believe me that freshwater fish get that big in Ontario.. until I showered her these pics.  She's going to think twice before letting her Yorkie go for a swim!  cheers
ill think about it...  leaning towards yes...
Some beauties there Mike.  Congrats, haven't fished down that way in years, time for me to get back there.  Thanks for sharing.  Jim
OH MAN So worth the blood. Thanks fer the sweet dreams.
I wish the St.Lawrence was in my backyard.
That was 2 hours VERY well spent.

Well... Tonight was the start of my break from walleye...  For the next month or so I'm going to be targeting lunge...  And tonight was a great start... We boated 3 musky in 2 hours...  1 trolling and 2 casting  And the big girl hit boatside before my buddy could even start a figure 8... We both saw the take... It was intense  They were 50-40-40 inches                  And my reward...
Sweeeeet!!!
Man, that is just awesome.
Very nice looking Ski congrats and a great way to start the fall hunt
That is a great night of musky fishing...congratulations.
I believe I recognize that spot in your first picture....Isn't that "Lake I Don't Know"...LOL.....  GREAT NIGHT on the water....KEEP POSTING PICS.  Bob
beauty fish  thanks for posting
WTG Mike !!!!!!!!!!!!That fish is as big as little Zach Give him a high 5 for me.  Paul
I'am moving back to Cornwall dam it !.....lol... Thats good fishing Mike ....
I know... He makes it look way bigger... But it was the thickest fish I've ever caught... And heavy...  Here's one of me holding it... Still looks huge
wow incredible night you guys had, congrats! that 50incher is a real solid lookin fish
Now that is a beatiful ski for sure  Nice war wound
WooooHOOOO!  Great shot of that tank....nice way to kick things off
Nice fish.
that 50 is a hog!!! congrats dude and thanks for posting the report
Sweet fish! The patterns on them are really nice too. Can't wait to get out there and learn a thing or two from a musky whisperer.
NICE!!!! And a scar to prove it to boot!!

it was really cool watching her hit boatside as well... we dont see that around here very often due to clear water conditions... thats the first ski ive seen boatside on the larry...  buddy was shaking the rest of the night....
A great fish you caught there. Congrats.
Magnificent (there's a word I don't often use) musky!!!  Nothing wrong with the 40"er either!
Wow ! Nice fish there. And you want to get into steelhead fishing ?
cant fish musky from dec 15 to 3rd saturday in june...  and walleye are closed till early-mid may...  sooooo... i thought id try steelhead...
Really nice fish there Mike!! what a fatty, hopefully we can put one or two in the boat this weekend!!
I'd be shaking like a leaf as well if I caught that tank.
hope i get to meet you guys when you come down...
